    <div class="prose max-w-none text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed" set:html='# AI Search Agency and Business Visibility\n\nAI search visibility is the likelihood that your business is selected, cited, or recommended inside AI generated answers. It is not based on keyword rankings or classic search positions.\n\nAI platforms evaluate clarity of definition, authority reinforcement, and prompt alignment. Businesses are included when their expertise is recognisable and their meaning remains stable across pages.\n\nVisibility varies by prompt structure and platform design. The goal is not to rank higher, but to reduce ambiguity so AI systems can reference your business confidently when relevant.\n\n## Why Visibility Differs by Platform\n\n| Platform | Primary Behaviour | Visibility Variation Cause |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| ChatGPT | Synthesis from retrievable sources | Interpretive confidence threshold |\n| Gemini | Search integrated generation | Search index influence |\n| Claude | Context heavy synthesis | Answer framing differences |\n\n## What this category includes\n\n- Clear explanations of AI search\n- What an AI search agency does\n- How AI chooses which businesses to recommend\n- The shift from keyword ranking to meaning\n- What businesses need to fix before AI engines can trust them\n\n## Why this matters\n\nAI tools are now the first place people ask questions.\n\nIf you are invisible in these answers, your competitors win by default.\n\nUse this category to understand how AI search works and what you can do to influence it.\n\n[Authority Guide **The Complete Guide to AI Search Visibility** \\\\\n\\\\\nLearn how to become visible and recommended in ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity and other AI search engines.](https://www.rank4ai.co.uk/ai-search/guides/complete-guide)\n\n## Key Topics\n\n- [How AI search differs from traditional SEO](https://www.rank4ai.co.uk/ai-seo/ai-seo-vs-traditional-seo)\n- [Why AI struggles with vague websites](https://www.rank4ai.